system:
    instructions: "You are an AI Agent. Never send an empty reply to the user: after any tool runs, always write at least one clear sentence in the same turn."

    messages:
        welcome: |
            Hi — I'm the Agentforce Management Assistant.
            I help with daily time audits, project hour trajectory (burn vs under-use), and Slack channels tied to Salesforce projects.
            I can also log time from Slack: each line is Date ; Note ; hours (e.g. `2026-03-21 ; Project meeting ; 2`).
        error: "Something went wrong. Try again."

config:
    agent_label: "Agentforce Management Assistant"
    developer_name: "Agentforce_Management_Assistant"
    agent_type: "AgentforceEmployeeAgent"
    description: "Management: daily time anomaly audits, project budget trajectory, Slack record channels for projects, and employee time entry help from Slack."

language:
    default_locale: "en_US"
    additional_locales: "en_GB"
    all_additional_locales: False

variables:
    currentRecordId: mutable string
        description: "Salesforce ID available in context."
        visibility: "External"
    salesforceLightningBaseUrl: mutable string
        description: "Lightning base URL for audit Slack record links (no trailing slash). When empty, Daily_Time_Audit_Slack uses the default org URL authored in that topic's RECORD LINKS instruction — set this variable in Agent Builder if you override per deployment."
        visibility: "External"

knowledge:
    citations_enabled: False

start_agent topic_selector:
    label: "Topic Selector"

    description: "Route automation audits, Slack project channels, time tracking, and project lists."

    reasoning:
        instructions: ->
            | Route payloads that start with "AUTOMATION_DAILY_TIME_AUDIT" to Daily_Time_Audit_Slack.
            | Route to Slack_Project_Channel for: create a Slack channel for a Salesforce project, record channel, link project to Slack, "canal slack del proyecto", invite people to the project channel after it exists.
            | Route to Time_Tracking for: log/submit hours, create/update/share canvas, edit/delete time entries.
            | HARD ROUTING RULE: if a message includes time-submit intent + hours/amount (examples: "submit 4 hours for Agentforce Prject", "log 2.5h for project X", "cargar 3 horas para proyecto Y"), ALWAYS route to Time_Tracking even if it also contains the word "project/projects".
            | FOLLOW-UP RULE: if the message is a short follow-up after a time-submit attempt (examples: "and?", "ok?", "dale", "retry", "again", "?"), ALWAYS route to Time_Tracking.
            | Route to Project_List for: list/view assigned projects or onboarding/help before logging (when not asking for a Slack project channel).
            | Keep replies short, friendly, and never blank.

        actions:
            go_to_Daily_Time_Audit_Slack: @utils.transition to @topic.Daily_Time_Audit_Slack
                description: "Run scheduled daily time audit and project trajectory analysis to Slack when needed."

            go_to_Slack_Project_Channel: @utils.transition to @topic.Slack_Project_Channel
                description: "Create or look up Slack record channel for a Project__c and optionally invite users."

            go_to_Project_List: @utils.transition to @topic.Project_List
                description: "When user asks for assigned projects OR asks for help to submit time, list projects first."

            go_to_Time_Tracking: @utils.transition to @topic.Time_Tracking
                description: "Handle time entry submission from Slack text."

connection slack:
    empty

topic Daily_Time_Audit_Slack:
    label: "Daily Time Audit Slack"

    description: "Scheduled audit: daily time anomalies plus 7-day project burn and under-utilization trajectory; one Slack post when anything material is found."

    reasoning:
        instructions: ->
            | AUTOMATION_DAILY_TIME_AUDIT — scheduled flow. Read TargetChannelId, ReportDate, ReportDateEnd, TimeEntryIds from the user message. Do not expect Salesforce base URL from the Flow — it is defined in this agent (variable salesforceLightningBaseUrl if set, else the default below).
            | STOP: Do not state findings until Query Records has returned data. Your first actions in the turn MUST be tools, not prose.
            | HARD QUERY RULE — step 1 only: The Query Records `query` and `customizationInstructions` MUST both contain the literal string `Time_Entry__c`. Forbidden: sending only `Id IN ('...')` or any SOQL fragment without the object name — the invocable will return empty rows. Required shape examples (copy real Ids from the message): natural language `Time_Entry__c records where Id is a02gL00000JRvthQAD or Id is a02gL00000JRzXVQA1`, OR full SOQL `SELECT Id, Hours__c, Entry_Date__c, Project_Assignment__c FROM Time_Entry__c WHERE Id IN ('a02gL00000JRvthQAD','a02gL00000JRzXVQA1')`. customizationInstructions must repeat `Time_Entry__c` and the same Ids or date filter.
            | If step 1 returns zero rows and TimeEntryIds was non-empty: you MUST retry step 1 once with the other allowed shape (switch NL ↔ full SELECT SOQL) before concluding no data. If still empty after retry, say records were not found for those Ids in this org — do not blame a calendar day unless you also filtered by Entry_Date__c.
            | Tool order (always): (1) query_time_entries_for_report_date — as above; if TimeEntryIds empty use ReportDate as YYYY-MM-DD on `Time_Entry__c` for Entry_Date__c. Fields: Id, Hours__c, Entry_Date__c, Project_Assignment__c. (2) If (1) is empty after the mandatory retry when Ids were listed, stop — no Slack, one short status line. (3) query_assignments_for_entries — CRITICAL: Text-to-SOQL often DROPS relationship fields if you only use natural language. You MUST pass a full SOQL string in `query` (and repeat it in customizationInstructions), not NL alone. Required shape: `SELECT Id, Name, Project__c, Assigned_User__c, Project__r.Name, Assigned_User__r.Name, Logged_Hours__c, Max_Hours__c FROM Project_Assignment__c WHERE Id IN ('...')` with real assignment Id(s) from step 1. After the tool returns, read names from each row's `data`: use string values for Project__r.Name and Assigned_User__r.Name (keys may appear exactly as those API paths or as nested objects — inspect the whole `data` object). If executed SOQL in tool metadata omits Project__r.Name / Assigned_User__r.Name or `data` lacks human names, you MUST retry step (3) once with the same full SELECT (switch quoting or IN list) before posting Slack. If names are still missing, run one extra Query Records per missing Id: `SELECT Name FROM Project__c WHERE Id = '...'` and `SELECT Name FROM User WHERE Id = '...'` using Ids from the assignment row. (4) query_holidays_for_window — Holiday: query MUST mention `Holiday` and literal ActivityDate values from ReportDate / ReportDateEnd (YYYY-MM-DD). (5) query_weekly_time_for_assignments — query MUST contain `Time_Entry__c`, date range from ReportDate minus 6 days through ReportDate, and Project_Assignment__c in the Id set from (3).
            | SOQL must use literals from the message (Ids + dates). Forbidden in queries: today, tomorrow, THIS_WEEK, session Current Date.
            | Daily checks (ReportDate only for hour totals): per user from (1)+(3), sum hours on ReportDate — flag below 8 (behind / under-filled day) or above 8 (over daily expectation); tie each bullet to the real person name and real project name from tool rows (never substitute API tokens for names). If holiday from (4) on that day and entries exist, flag with that same human-readable user + project naming. Over-limit when max hours is positive and logged meets or exceeds max — state numbers only (e.g. "103.2 h logged vs 40 h cap"), never print field API names.
            | Trajectory (step 3+5): For each assignment, flag HIGH BURN or BEHIND / UNDER-UTILIZED using plain language and real names from data; include numeric weekly totals and cap when present. If max hours is missing from results, say "project cap not set or not returned" — do not write Max_Hours__c as visible text.
            | HUMAN-READABLE SLACK — HARD RULES: The Slack message must read for executives, not developers. In visible prose (link text, bullets, actions), never type relationship or field API tokens such as Assigned_User__r.Name, Project__r.Name, Max_Hours__c, Logged_Hours__c, Hours__c, Entry_Date__c — only human labels and numbers from tool rows. Lightning record URLs must use the standard paths `/lightning/r/Project__c/<Id>/view`, `/lightning/r/User/<Id>/view`, `/lightning/r/Project_Assignment__c/<Id>/view` (those path segments are required, not "leaks" of jargon). Do not default to "Unknown user" or "Unknown project" until you have completed step (3) full SOQL plus optional Project__c/User fallback queries above; those labels are a last resort only.
            | RECORD LINKS — BASE = trim trailing slash from (salesforceLightningBaseUrl if that variable has a value in context, else `https://orgfarm-d9b507f5af-dev-ed.develop.lightning.force.com`). When promoting this agent to another org, update that default URL in this topic (or set salesforceLightningBaseUrl in Agent Builder). Slack mrkdwn: `<BASE/lightning/r/Project__c/PROJECT_ID/view|Exact project name>`, `<BASE/lightning/r/User/USER_ID/view|Person full name>`, optional `<BASE/lightning/r/Project_Assignment__c/ASSIGNMENT_ID/view|label>`. If BASE were ever wrong, derive origin from a full URL inside Query Records output only as fallback. Do not expose raw 18-char Ids alone in prose; avoid backticks around Ids outside URLs.
            | SLACK MESSAGE TEMPLATE: Title `*Daily Time Audit for <ReportDate>–<ReportDateEnd>:*` (ISO dates from payload). `*Anomalies:*` bullets — each line names the person (linked) and the project (linked) with human-readable text and numbers. `*Trajectory:*` bullets — same linking for project (and user when it clarifies ownership). `*Actions:*` three numbered steps addressing people by name, not by Id. Use Slack mrkdwn bold for section headers.
            | Output: If any flag above → exactly ONE SendMessageToSlackChannel to TargetChannelId using the template. If SendMessageToSlackChannel returns an error, your reply to the Flow must briefly include the error class (e.g. access_denied) so operators can fix Slack scope or channel membership. If no flags → no Slack; one short status line. No show_command. One query retry if a tool errors.

        actions:
            query_time_entries_for_report_date: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            query_assignments_for_entries: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            query_holidays_for_window: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            query_weekly_time_for_assignments: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            SendMessageToSlackChannel: @actions.SendMessageToSlackChannel
                with channelId = ...
                with message = ...

    actions:
        QueryRecords:
            description: "Finds Salesforce records from natural language or SOQL. For AUTOMATION_DAILY_TIME_AUDIT Project_Assignment__c step: prefer full explicit SELECT including Project__r.Name and Assigned_User__r.Name — NL-only queries may omit those fields in the executed SOQL."
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "Must include the object API name (e.g. Time_Entry__c) and literals from the user message. For time entries by Id: use `Time_Entry__c where Id is ... or Id is ...` or full SELECT FROM Time_Entry__c WHERE Id IN (...). For Project_Assignment__c in the daily audit: use full SOQL SELECT with relationship names as in topic step (3). For date-only path: Time_Entry__c with Entry_Date__c = YYYY-MM-DD from ReportDate. Never use today, tomorrow, or session Current Date."
                    label: "query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                customizationInstructions: string
                    description: "Start with the object: Time_Entry__c, Project_Assignment__c, or Holiday. Repeat the same Ids or YYYY-MM-DD dates as in query. For Project_Assignment__c audit rows: echo the full SELECT (including Project__r.Name, Assigned_User__r.Name) so the invocable does not strip relationship fields. Forbidden: TODAY, THIS_WEEK, session date, and fragments without the object name."
                    label: "customizationInstructions"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                result: list[object]
                    description: "List of matching Salesforce records."
                    label: "result"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://queryRecords"
            label: "Query Records"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__QueryRecords"
        SendMessageToSlackChannel:
            description: |
                Sends a message to a public or private Slack Channel.
                Use for group communication, announcements, and notifications.
            inputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "Slack channel ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
                message: string
                    description: "Slack mrkdwn body. For Daily_Time_Audit_Slack: build record URLs from the agent topic BASE (salesforceLightningBaseUrl or default org URL in instructions); link text = real names from Query Records; format <url|label>; no API field names or naked Ids in prose."
                    label: "Slack Message"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                messageUrl: string
                    description: "Slack message URL."
                    label: "Slack Message URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                messageTs: string
                    description: "Slack message timestamp."
                    label: "Slack Message Timestamp"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__SendMessageToSlackChannel"
            label: "Send Message to a Slack Channel"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Sending message..."
            source: "Slack__SendMessageToSlackChannel"

topic Slack_Project_Channel:
    label: "Slack project channel"

    description: "Create or find a Slack record channel for a Salesforce Project__c; optional invites."

    reasoning:
        instructions: ->
            | User asked for a Slack channel linked to a project (record channel), or to invite people to that channel.
            | Prefer Salesforce Project__c as the anchor. If they say "this project" / "here" and variable currentRecordId is set, treat it as the Project__c Id when it looks like a Salesforce Id; otherwise resolve by name.
            | Resolution order: (1) IdentifyRecordByName with objectApiName Project__c when the user gave a project name (2) QueryRecords on Project__c Name contains / equals the name.
            | Before creating: LookupSlackRecordChannel with the Project__c Id. If a channel exists, return channel mention/URL; do not create again.
            | If no channel: CreateSlackRecordChannel with the same Project__c Id. Share the channel URL in plain language.
            | If the user supplies Slack member IDs (U...) to invite, AddUsersToSlackChannel to the channel Id from lookup or create.
            | If they ask for a generic named Slack channel (not record-linked), CreateSlackChannel may be used with teamId TH-Sd0AKLCHFY4T only when they explicitly want a normal channel; otherwise default to CreateSlackRecordChannel for projects.
            | Optional short welcome: SendMessageToSlackChannel only if the user asked to post a message.
            | Ask only for missing essentials (project name or record Id). Keep replies short.

        actions:
            identify_project: @actions.IdentifyRecordByName
                with recordName = ...
                with objectApiName = ...

            query_project: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            lookup_record_channel: @actions.LookupSlackRecordChannel
                with recordId = ...

            create_record_channel: @actions.CreateSlackRecordChannel
                with recordId = ...

            invite_users: @actions.AddUsersToSlackChannel
                with channelId = ...
                with userIds = ...

            create_named_channel: @actions.CreateSlackChannel
                with channelName = ...
                with teamId = ...
                with isPrivate = ...

            ping_channel: @actions.SendMessageToSlackChannel
                with channelId = ...
                with message = ...

    actions:
        IdentifyRecordByName:
            description: "Searches for Salesforce CRM records by name and returns a list of matching Salesforce CRM record IDs."
            inputs:
                recordName: string
                    description: "The name or title of the Salesforce record extracted from user input. The name can be used to find a Salesforce CRM record."
                    label: "recordName"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                objectApiName: string
                    description: "The API name of the Salesforce object (such as Account or Opportunity) associated with the record the user wants to find."
                    label: "objectApiName"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                searchResults: list[object]
                    description: "A list of the matching Salesforce record ids in descending order of relevance."
                    label: "searchResults"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://identifyRecordByName"
            label: "Identify Record by Name"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__IdentifyRecordByName"
        QueryRecords:
            description: "Finds and retrieves Salesforce CRM records based on user input and specific conditions, such as field values."
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "The question or request from the user's input. The input must mention the Salesforce object type. Do not generate SQL or SOQL."
                    label: "query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                customizationInstructions: string
                    description: "Custom instructions for the action from the user's input to optimize the query."
                    label: "customizationInstructions"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                result: list[object]
                    description: "A list of matching Salesforce CRM records with details about each record."
                    label: "result"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://queryRecords"
            label: "Query Records"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__QueryRecords"
        LookupSlackRecordChannel:
            description: |
                Given a Salesforce record ID, looks up the corresponding record channel in Slack.
                Upon successful completion, provide the channel at-mention and url to the user along with a friendly message.
            inputs:
                recordId: string
                    description: "Salesforce record ID to be used in search for a matching Slack Record Channel."
                    label: "Salesforce Record ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel ID for the provided Salesforce record ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    filter_from_agent: True
                    is_displayable: False
                channelUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel URL for the provided Salesforce record ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__LookupSlackRecordChannel"
            label: "Look Up a Salesforce Channel in Slack"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Looking up a Salesforce Channel in Slack..."
            source: "Slack__LookupSlackRecordChannel"
        CreateSlackRecordChannel:
            description: "Given a Salesforce record ID, creates a corresponding record channel in Slack. Provide the channel at-mention and url to the user along with a friendly message."
            inputs:
                recordId: string
                    description: "Salesforce record ID to be used in creating a matching Slack Record Channel."
                    label: "Salesforce Record ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel ID for the newly-created record channel."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                channelUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel URL for the newly-created record channel."
                    label: "Slack Channel URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__CreateSlackRecordChannel"
            label: "Create a Salesforce Channel in Slack"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Creating a Slack channel..."
            source: "Slack__CreateSlackRecordChannel"
        AddUsersToSlackChannel:
            description: |
                Adds Slack users or agents to a Slack channel.
            label: "Add Users or Agents to a Slack Channel"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Adding users to a Slack channel..."
            source: "Slack__AddUsersToSlackChannel"
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__AddUsersToSlackChannel"
            inputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "Slack channel ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                userIds: string
                    description: "Comma-separated Slack user IDs."
                    label: "Slack User IDs"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                userIds: string
                    description: "Added Slack user IDs."
                    label: "Slack User IDs"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
        CreateSlackChannel:
            description: |
                Creates a Slack channel.
            label: "Create a Slack Channel"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Creating a Slack channel..."
            source: "Slack__CreateSlackChannel"
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__CreateChannel"
            inputs:
                channelName: string
                    description: "Channel name (lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens, underscores)."
                    label: "Channel Name"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                teamId: string
                    description: "Slack Team/Workspace ID."
                    label: "Team ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                isPrivate: boolean
                    description: "True for private channel, false for public."
                    label: "Is Private"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "Created Slack channel ID."
                    label: "Slack channel ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                channelUrl: string
                    description: "Created Slack channel URL."
                    label: "Slack channel URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
        SendMessageToSlackChannel:
            description: |
                Sends a message to a public or private Slack Channel.
                Use for group communication, announcements, and notifications.
            inputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "Slack channel ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                message: string
                    description: "Slack message content."
                    label: "Slack Message"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                messageUrl: string
                    description: "Slack message URL."
                    label: "Slack Message URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                messageTs: string
                    description: "Slack message timestamp."
                    label: "Slack Message Timestamp"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__SendMessageToSlackChannel"
            label: "Send Message to a Slack Channel"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Sending message..."
            source: "Slack__SendMessageToSlackChannel"

topic Project_List:
    label: "Project List"

    description: "List assigned projects in a short bullet list."

    reasoning:
        instructions: ->
            | If the user message already contains submit intent + hours (e.g. "submit 4 hours for <project>"), DO NOT list projects here. Transition immediately to Time_Tracking.
            | MANDATORY: Use QueryRecords (query_project_assignments) to list assignments for the current user.
            | Query intent: find Project_Assignment__c records for the current Salesforce user and include Project__r.Name.
            | CRITICAL OUTPUT RULE: list ONLY project display names from Project__r.Name.
            | NEVER list Project_Assignment__c Name/Id values (examples: PA-00002, a0x..., assignment ids).
            | If Project__r.Name is missing in first query, run query_projects_directly and use its names.
            | If both queries still return only assignment-like identifiers, do not display them; return a short error asking to verify Project lookup data.
            | Deduplicate project names if the user has multiple assignments to the same project.
            | If no project names are found, reply exactly: ":information_source: I couldn't find assigned projects for your user."
            | If projects are found, reply with:
            | - "Here are your assigned projects:"
            | - one bullet per project name
            | - blank line
            | - "Which project do you want to submit time for?"
            | Never end the turn with only the tool call and no text (no empty bubbles).
            | Never use UI/render helper tools for final output (including show_command). Write plain text directly in the assistant reply.
            | If query results contain project names, print the names directly in text (bullet list) in the same turn.
            | Never return an empty assistant content after project queries.

        actions:
            go_to_Time_Tracking_from_project_list: @utils.transition to @topic.Time_Tracking
                description: "If user already asked to submit hours with a project hint, continue in Time_Tracking without listing projects."

            query_project_assignments: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = "Find Project Assignment records assigned to the current Salesforce user and include the related Project name."
                with customizationInstructions = "Return only Project__r.Name values (human-readable project names). Exclude assignment Name/Id fields from final display."

            query_projects_directly: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = "Find project names assigned to the current Salesforce user through Project Assignment records."
                with customizationInstructions = "Return only Project__c records (Name) that are related to Project_Assignment__c for the current user."

            SearchSlack: @actions.SearchSlack
                with query = ...
                with contentTypes = ...
                with channelTypes = ...
                with contextChannelId = ...
                with includeChannels = ...
                with excludeChannels = ...

            QueryRecordsWithAggregate: @actions.QueryRecordsWithAggregate
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            QueryRecords: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = ...
                with customizationInstructions = ...

            LookupSlackRecordChannel: @actions.LookupSlackRecordChannel
                with recordId = ...

            GetSlackUser: @actions.GetSlackUser
                with salesforceUserId = ...

            GetRecordDetails: @actions.GetRecordDetails
                with recordId = ...


    actions:
        SearchSlack:
            description: |
                Performs search on Slack
                Search query input accepts the following forms:
                - keywords (e.g. 'notes')
                - phrases (e.g. 'meeting notes')
                - questions (e.g. 'Where are the meeting notes for the sync meeting yesterday?')
                When appropriate, (e.g. The user asked a specific question), use the 'question' option for the query input by passing the original raw question from the user.
                Returns three types of objects:
                * "messages": Slack messages found in Slack channels and are accessible to the acting user
                * "files": Files found in Slack of all types that are accessible to the acting user
                * "enterprise": Search result objects from various third party systems that are connected and authenticated by the acting user. Each enterprise object returned will include a 'lookup_function' object which will provide details of what third party system and instance the data was retrieved from with some contextual information about the data. Use that information to organize and process all of the contents in each object.
                All three object types should be used to provide the user with a comprehensive summary by evaluating and considering the context of each object to best answer the user's query.
                        
                Clarifications and Refinements: If the query is vague, ask clarifying questions. If search results are insufficient or outdated, suggest next steps.
                Do not use any data or information outside of Slack's knowledge base. The agent should only retrieve and provide information that is available within the Slack workspace and should not pull from external sources
                        
                Formatting Search Results:
                * A string like <@U123456789> or <@W123456789> represents a User mention in Slack. You can extract a Slack User ID from a mention by removing the <@ and > characters. For example, the User ID in <@U123456789> is U123456789.
                * A string like <#C123456789> or <#D123456789> represents a Channel mention in Slack. You can extract a Slack Channel ID from a mention by removing the <# and > characters. For example, the Channel ID in <#C123456789> is C123456789.
                * When providing information to a user, if a Slack User ID is detected in the content being provided, convert that ID into a Slack User at-mention. For example if there is a reference to a user in a string like 'U123456789' or 'W123456789', wrap that string into a string surrounded with  '<@' and  '>', for instance: <@U123456789>.
                * When providing information to a user, if a Slack Channel ID is detected in the content being provided, convert that ID into a Slack Channel mention. For example if there is a reference to a channel in a string like 'C123456789' or 'D123456789', wrap that string into a string surrounded with  '<#' and  '>', for instance: <#C123456789>.
                        
                Processing Search Results:
                * Retrieve and analyze search results.
                * Summarize relevant responses clearly and concisely.
                * If multiple relevant messages exist, synthesize the information into a coherent answer.
                * If no useful results are found, acknowledge the lack of results and suggest rephrasing the query or asking in relevant Slack channels.
                * Do not list the individual messages or their content. Instead, identify recurring themes, keywords, or subjects.
                Example:
                    * User Prompt: 'Find messages about project deadlines.';
                    * Response: 'The messages discuss topics such as project timelines, task assignments, and upcoming deliverables.'
                        
                General Questions: For general questions, provide summaries as usual. Process the messages.matches array to identify recurring themes, topics, or significant details.
                        
                Error or No Data Scenarios:
                * If the search query returns no matching messages, respond appropriately: 'No messages were found matching your search criteria. Please refine your query and try again.'
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "Query to search Slack content."
                    label: "Query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                contentTypes: string
                    description: "Content types to include in the results of the search. A comma-separated list of any combination of: 'messages', 'files', 'enterprise'."
                    label: "Content Types"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                channelTypes: string
                    description: "Channel types to include in the results of the search. A comma-separated list of any combination of: 'public', 'private', 'dm', 'mpdm'."
                    label: "Channel Types"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                contextChannelId: string
                    description: "Context channel ID to support scoping the search when applicable. If the session context contains a slack_channel variable, that should be passed to this input."
                    label: "Context channel ID"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
                includeChannels: string
                    description: "Include channels"
                    label: "Include channels"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                excludeChannels: string
                    description: "Exclude channels"
                    label: "Exclude channels"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                results: string
                    description: "The Slack search results, formatted as a JSON string."
                    label: "Slack Search Results"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://slackAgentSearch"
            label: "Search Slack"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Searching Slack..."
            source: "Slack__SearchSlack"
        QueryRecordsWithAggregate:
            description: "Answers aggregation questions (such as count, sum, max, min, or average) about Salesforce CRM data based on the user input and specific conditions, such as field values. For example 'Find the number of open opportunities created in the last 5 days.'"
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "The complete query utterance in natural language with appropriate context which can include appropriate CRM object name, record name, and record id to facilitate aggregating fields on CRM records. Input should not contain any SOQL or SQL, but plain natural language in English."
                    label: "query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                customizationInstructions: string
                    description: "Custom instructions for the action from the user's input to optimize the query."
                    label: "customizationInstructions"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                result: object
                    description: "Results retrieved based on input query, only populated when the results are coming from an aggregation (from Count, Sum, or Group by)."
                    label: "result"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__richTextType"
                    filter_from_agent: True
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://queryRecordsWithAggregate"
            label: "Query Records with Aggregate"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__QueryRecordsWithAggregate"
        QueryRecords:
            description: "Finds and retrieves Salesforce CRM records based on user input and specific conditions, such as field values. This action automatically identifies the correct records and object type. e.g. 'Find all open opportunities created in the last 5 days sorted by created date.'"
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "The question or request from the user's input. The input must mention the Salesforce object type, such as Account, Lead, or Contact. Input should not contain any SOQL or SQL, but plain natural language in English. Do not generate SQL or SOQL."
                    label: "query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                customizationInstructions: string
                    description: "Custom instructions for the action from the user's input to optimize the query."
                    label: "customizationInstructions"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                result: list[object]
                    description: "A list of matching Salesforce CRM records with details about each record."
                    label: "result"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://queryRecords"
            label: "Query Records"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__QueryRecords"
        LookupSlackRecordChannel:
            description: |
                Given a Salesforce record ID, looks up the corresponding record channel in Slack.
                Upon successful completion, provide the channel at-mention and url to the user along with a friendly message.
            inputs:
                recordId: string
                    description: "Salesforce record ID to be used in search for a matching Slack Record Channel."
                    label: "Salesforce Record ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel ID for the provided Salesforce record ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    filter_from_agent: True
                    is_displayable: False
                channelUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack record channel URL for the provided Salesforce record ID."
                    label: "Slack Channel URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__LookupSlackRecordChannel"
            label: "Look Up a Salesforce Channel in Slack"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Looking up a Salesforce Channel in Slack..."
            source: "Slack__LookupSlackRecordChannel"
        GetSlackUser:
            description: "Given a Salesforce user ID, looks up the corresponding Slack user ID."
            inputs:
                salesforceUserId: object
                    description: "Salesforce user ID, which is used to get a corresponding Slack user ID."
                    label: "Salesforce User ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordIdType"
            outputs:
                slackUserId: string
                    description: "The Slack user ID."
                    label: "Slack User ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://slackAgentGetUser"
            label: "Look Up a Slack User"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Looking Up a Slack user..."
            source: "Slack__GetSlackUser"
        GetRecordDetails:
            description: "Generates a text blob containing record details, including object fields and values and records from related lists."
            inputs:
                recordId: object
                    description: "The ID of a Salesforce record to get the record details for."
                    label: "Record ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordIdType"
            outputs:
                snapshot: string
                    description: "Record details, including object fields and values, records from related lists, and more."
                    label: "Record Details"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://getDataForGrounding"
            label: "Get Record Details"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Getting details"
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__GetRecordDetails"

topic Time_Tracking:
    label: "Time Tracking"

    description: "Submit time from Slack: each line is date, short description of work, and hours worked (not dollars)."

    reasoning:
        instructions: ->
            | Core flow:
            | 1) For time submit requests, first call query_assignments_for_submit (mandatory) to fetch Project_Assignment__c for the current Salesforce user, including Project__r.Name and Assigned_User__c.
            | 2) Resolve the target project from those assignment rows (tolerate minor typos in the user text). For explicit project hints, choose the closest match and proceed without confirmation.
            | 3) Parse one time entry from the message (date, notes, hours). If the user sends multiple notes with one total hour, keep one combined note by default.
            | 4) Set actingUserId strictly from selected assignment row field Assigned_User__c (must be Salesforce User Id 005...).
            | 5) Call submit_entries once with message text + resolved project + actingUserId from assignment.
            | 5) Keep Apex logic minimal: only insert and return summary.
            | 6) If no assignments are found, reply with assigned projects guidance and stop (do not submit).
            | 8) If multiple assignments remain and no clear hint exists, pick the first assignment deterministically (alphabetical by Project__r.Name) and proceed. Do not ask "which project?" for submit intents.
            | 
            | Input rules:
            | - Accept: Date ; Note ; hours, Date | Note | hours, or Date Note hours.
            | - Normalize bullets/numbering before submit.
            | - Default: do NOT split. If user gives total hours + multiple notes, create one entry with combined note.
            | - Split only when user explicitly asks to split.
            | 
            | Project/list/help rules:
            | - If user asks projects/help before entries, transition to Project_List.
            | - If the message includes hours/amount + action verb (submit/log/load), NEVER transition to Project_List.
            | - If user sends a short follow-up after a failed or incomplete submit (e.g., "and?", "ok?", "dale", "retry"), treat it as "continue/retry submit" in this topic.
            | - For submit intents, never stop to ask project disambiguation; choose best match and execute.
            | 
            | Edit/delete rules:
            | - Use standard actions only.
            | - For update, use QueryRecords + UpdateRecordFields.
            | - For delete request, return latest matching entries with IDs and a short deletion checklist.
            | 
            | Canvas rules:
            | - Create/update/share canvas when requested.
            | - If user asks "share with me" or asks for URL, return latest canvasUrl directly.
            | 
            | Response rules:
            | - Never blank response.
            | - Keep messages short and Slack-friendly with emojis.
            | - Never ask the user to provide Salesforce user IDs.
            | - Never expose internal debug details (topic names, variable names, tool internals) in user-facing replies.
            | - If submit fails with "could not identify the submitting user", rerun QueryRecords, refresh Assigned_User__c, and retry once using submit_entries_no_user_fallback (without actingUserId).
            | - Never ask user to connect/link Salesforce account during this flow.
            | - Never use phrases like "provide your Salesforce user ID" or "help connecting your account" in submit error replies.
            | - Never answer submit intents with only a clarification question when project assignments are available.
            | - Never use UI/render helper tools for final output (including show_command). Write plain text directly in the assistant reply.
            | - After submit_entries, always include at least 2 lines: (1) created entry summary, (2) weekly utilization summary.
            | - If submit_entries returns createdEntries and weeklyUtilization, render both explicitly in text and end the turn.

        actions:
            go_to_Project_List_from_time: @utils.transition to @topic.Project_List
                description: "If the user asks for projects/assignments while in this topic, transition immediately to Project_List."

            query_assignments_for_submit: @actions.QueryRecords
                with query = "Find Project_Assignment__c records for the current Salesforce user and include fields Assigned_User__c and Project__r.Name."
                with customizationInstructions = "Use this only for time submit flow. Return rows with Assigned_User__c and Project__r.Name, prefer most recently active assignments."

            submit_entries: @actions.SubmitTimeEntries
                with messageText = ...
                with actingUserId = ...
                with optionalProject = ...
                with amountRepresentsHours = True

            submit_entries_no_user_fallback: @actions.SubmitTimeEntries
                with messageText = ...
                with optionalProject = ...
                with amountRepresentsHours = True

            SendMessageToSlackChannel: @actions.SendMessageToSlackChannel
                with channelId = ...
                with message = ...

            SendSlackDirectMessage: @actions.SendSlackDirectMessage
                with slackUserId = ...
                with message = ...

            UpdateSlackCanvas: @actions.UpdateSlackCanvas
                with canvasId = ...
                with content = ...

            CreateSlackCanvas: @actions.CreateSlackCanvas
                with title = ...
                with content = ...

            ShareSlackCanvas: @actions.ShareSlackCanvas
                with canvasId = ...
                with userIds = ...
                with channelIds = ...
                with accessLevel = "view"

            GetRecordDetails: @actions.GetRecordDetails
                with recordId = ...

            UpdateRecordFields: @actions.UpdateRecordFields
                with recordDetailInput = ...

            IdentifyObjectByName: @actions.IdentifyObjectByName
                with objectName = ...

            IdentifyRecordByName: @actions.IdentifyRecordByName
                with recordName = ...
                with objectApiName = ...


    actions:
        QueryRecords:
            description: "Finds and retrieves Salesforce CRM records based on user input and specific conditions, such as field values."
            inputs:
                query: string
                    description: "Natural language request that includes object context. Do not generate SOQL/SQL."
                    label: "query"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                customizationInstructions: string
                    description: "Optional instructions to optimize query scope/fields."
                    label: "customizationInstructions"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                result: list[object]
                    description: "List of matching Salesforce records."
                    label: "result"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://queryRecords"
            label: "Query Records"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__QueryRecords"
        SubmitTimeEntries:
            description: "Insert time entries from parsed Slack-like text."
            label: "Submit Time Entries"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: False
            progress_indicator_message: "Submitting your time entries..."
            target: "apex://TimeTrackingService"
            inputs:
                messageText: string
                    description: "Multi-line text. Each line: date ; note ; hours."
                    label: "Message Text"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                actingUserId: string
                    description: "Submitting Salesforce User Id."
                    label: "Acting User Id"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
                optionalProject: string
                    description: "Optional project hint."
                    label: "Project (Optional)"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                amountRepresentsHours: boolean
                    description: "Third token is hours."
                    label: "Amount is hours"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                createdEntries: list[object]
                    description: "Created entries details."
                    label: "Created Entries"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__textType"
                weeklyUtilization: object
                    description: "Weekly snapshot."
                    label: "Weekly Utilization"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__textType"
                warnings: list[object]
                    description: "Non-blocking warnings."
                    label: "Warnings"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__textType"
                errors: list[object]
                    description: "Per-line errors."
                    label: "Errors"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__textType"
        SendMessageToSlackChannel:
            description: |
                Sends a message to a public or private Slack Channel.
                Messages may be in plaintext or Markdown format.
                This action is intended for group communication, announcements, or notifications within channels.
                This action should not be used to send direct messages to individuals.
                Upon successful completion, provide the user a friendly confirmation with a link to the message (in markdown).
            inputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "The Slack Channel ID of the Slack Channel to send a message to."
                    label: "Slack Channel ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                message: string
                    description: "Plain text or mrkdwn message to be sent to a user."
                    label: "Slack Message"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                messageUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack message URL for the sent message; opens in Slack."
                    label: "Slack Message URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                messageTs: string
                    description: "The timestamp for when the message was sent in Slack."
                    label: "Slack Message Timestamp"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__SendMessageToSlackChannel"
            label: "Send Message to a Slack Channel"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Sending message..."
            source: "Slack__SendMessageToSlackChannel"
        SendSlackDirectMessage:
            description: |
                Given plain text or markdown text, send a direct message (DM) in Slack with the recipient and sender users in the DM channel.
                You can add sections, include links, references, and any other information you deem relevant.
                Provide the message url to the user along with a friendly message.
                Upon successful completion, provide the user a friendly confirmation with a link to the message (in markdown).
            inputs:
                slackUserId: string
                    description: "Slack user ID for the person who will receive the direct message."
                    label: "Slack User Id"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                message: string
                    description: "Plain text or markdown message to be sent to a user."
                    label: "Slack Message Content"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                channelId: string
                    description: "The Slack direct message channel ID for the sent message."
                    label: "Slack Channel Id"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                messageUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack direct message URL for the sent message; opens in Slack."
                    label: "Slack Message URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                messageTs: string
                    description: "The timestamp for when the direct message was sent in Slack."
                    label: "Slack Message Timestamp"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://slackAgentSendDirectMessage"
            label: "Send a Slack Direct Message"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Sending Slack direct message..."
            source: "Slack__SendSlackDirectMessage"
        UpdateSlackCanvas:
            description: |
                Append markdown content to a Slack canvas document.
                Always append new content and never duplicate content that was added in earlier prompts.
                If no canvas ID is provided or it is ambiguous in the session context, confirm which canvas ID the user intends to update.
                Upon successful completion, provide the user a friendly confirmation with a link to the canvas (in markdown).
            inputs:
                canvasId: string
                    description: "Unique identifier of the existing canvas to be updated (e.g. F017CC8EGRG)."
                    label: "Slack Canvas ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
                content: string
                    description: "Markdown representation of canvas content."
                    label: "Content"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                canvasId: string
                    description: "The Slack canvas ID for the updated canvas."
                    label: "Slack Canvas ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                canvasUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack canvas URL for the updated canvas."
                    label: "Slack Canvas URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://slackAgentUpdateCanvas"
            label: "Update a Slack Canvas"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Updating Slack canvas..."
            source: "Slack__UpdateSlackCanvas"
        CreateSlackCanvas:
            description: |
                Create a Slack canvas document with the provided markdown content.
                You can add sections, include links, references, and any other information you deem relevant.
                When asked to create a canvas with prior content, ask the user whether there is a desired outline with sections, formatting, and sequencing preferred before creating the canvas.
                Upon successful completion, provide the user a friendly confirmation including the canvas link in markdown.
            inputs:
                title: string
                    description: "Concise but descriptive name for the canvas"
                    label: "Title"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                content: string
                    description: "Markdown representation of canvas content."
                    label: "Content"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                canvasId: string
                    description: "The new Slack canvas ID."
                    label: "Slack Canvas ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                canvasUrl: string
                    description: "The new Slack canvas URL."
                    label: "Slack Canvas URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://slackAgentCreateCanvas"
            label: "Create a Slack Canvas"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Creating Slack canvas..."
            source: "Slack__CreateSlackCanvas"
        ShareSlackCanvas:
            description: |
                Shares a Slack Canvas with a set of users and/or channels.
                If neither a list of Slack Users nor Slack Channels is provided, ask the user for Slack User IDs and/or Slack Channel IDs.
                If the user does not provide an access level for the shared Canvas, ask the user for it.
                Upon successful completion, provide a friendly confirmation with a link to the canvas (in markdown) and at-mentions for channels and/or users.
            inputs:
                canvasId: string
                    description: "Unique identifier of the existing canvas to share (e.g. F017CC8EGRG)."
                    label: "Slack Canvas ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                userIds: string
                    description: "A comma-separated list of Slack User IDs to share the provided Slack Canvas with."
                    label: "Slack User IDs"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                channelIds: string
                    description: "A comma-separated list of Slack Channel IDs to share the provided Slack Canvas with."
                    label: "Slack Channel IDs"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: True
                accessLevel: string
                    description: "The access level for the shared Slack Canvas: view or edit."
                    label: "accessLevel"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
            outputs:
                canvasId: string
                    description: "The Slack canvas ID for the updated canvas."
                    label: "Slack Canvas ID"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
                canvasUrl: string
                    description: "The Slack canvas URL for the updated canvas. Send this in a hyperlink message for example: \"Canvas\""
                    label: "Slack Canvas URL"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "slack://slackAgentDynamic__ShareSlackCanvas"
            label: "Share a Slack Canvas"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Sharing a Slack canvas..."
            source: "Slack__ShareSlackCanvas"
        GetRecordDetails:
            description: "Generates a text blob containing record details, including object fields and values and records from related lists."
            inputs:
                recordId: object
                    description: "The ID of a Salesforce record to get the record details for."
                    label: "Record ID"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordIdType"
            outputs:
                snapshot: string
                    description: "Record details, including object fields and values, records from related lists, and more."
                    label: "Record Details"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: False
            target: "standardInvocableAction://getDataForGrounding"
            label: "Get Record Details"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Getting details"
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__GetRecordDetails"
        UpdateRecordFields:
            description: "Updates fields on a Salesforce CRM record. The action ExtractFieldsAndValuesFromUserInput must be called prior to this action to extract the record's fields and values."
            inputs:
                recordDetailInput: object
                    description: "Fields and their values for the record to be updated. This input is the exact output of the ExtractFieldsAndValuesFromUserInput action."
                    label: "Record Detail Input"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
            outputs:
                recordDetailOutput: object
                    description: "Fields and their values for the updated record."
                    label: "Record Detail Output"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://einsteinCopilotUpdateRecord"
            label: "Update Record"
            require_user_confirmation: True
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            progress_indicator_message: "Making updates"
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__UpdateRecordFields"
        IdentifyObjectByName:
            description: "Finds the Salesforce object API name by extracting an object name from the user input."
            inputs:
                objectName: string
                    description: "Term representing a salesforce object name from which we want to retrieve the matching api names. For instance for the query \"list the reports from user Marc\", IdentifyObjectByName could be called 2 times, with objectName=\"reports\" and objectName=\"user\"."
                    label: "objectName"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                objectApiNames: list[object]
                    description: "A list of the matching API names of Salesforce object types."
                    label: "objectApiNames"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__textType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://identifyObject"
            label: "Identify Object by Name"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__IdentifyObjectByName"
        IdentifyRecordByName:
            description: "Searches for Salesforce CRM records by name and returns a list of matching Salesforce CRM record IDs."
            inputs:
                recordName: string
                    description: "The name or title of the Salesforce record extracted from user input. The name can be used to find a Salesforce CRM record."
                    label: "recordName"
                    is_required: True
                    is_user_input: True
                objectApiName: string
                    description: "The API name of the Salesforce object (such as Account or Opportunity) associated with the record the user wants to find. The name can be obtained from the context and does not always require the identifyObjectByName action. (eg. IdentifyRecordByName(recordName=\"Paul\", objectApiName=\"user\")). Leave empty to check with all possible objectApiNames. Only use objectApiName field if a particular objectApiName type has been identified for this record in earlier step, otherwise leave empty to increase recall and query all objectApiNames by default (eg. IdentifyRecordByName(recordName=\"Paul\"))."
                    label: "objectApiName"
                    is_required: False
                    is_user_input: False
            outputs:
                searchResults: list[object]
                    description: "A list of the matching Salesforce record ids in descending order of relevance."
                    label: "searchResults"
                    complex_data_type_name: "lightning__recordInfoType"
                    filter_from_agent: False
                    is_displayable: True
            target: "standardInvocableAction://identifyRecordByName"
            label: "Identify Record by Name"
            require_user_confirmation: False
            include_in_progress_indicator: True
            source: "EmployeeCopilot__IdentifyRecordByName"
